metadata.name: fa37
metadata.description:
SHA-256 fingerprints are human fingerprints hiding an hexadecimal tattoo. This series is about the human transition from the physical world to the digital world. It is also about the convergence of the 2 worlds: the 4 digits tattooed on each fingerprint are also the start of the SHA-256 hash of each image.

The image of this NFT sits here: https://arweave.net/XoC94dmV3V9_apdPomI4njYw7Vxm47TGtIEjudrRsQo. You can check its SHA-256 hash at https://www.scratch-tech.com/sha256-file-checksum/ or with any other SHA-256 hash checker.
